comments.body:
Hi [~vvasudev],

Thanks for working on the patch, some comments:
- Memory/VCores should not be changeable configuration, otherwise it will create lots of compatibility issues. So could we handle memory/vcores separately? We could do: 
1) In ResourcePBImpl, don't need to handle configuration missing issue, such as:
{code}
  public int getMemory() {
    try {
      ResourceInformation ri =
          this.getResourceInformation(ResourceInformation.MEMORY_MB.getName());
      return (int) UnitsConversionUtil
          .convert(ri.getUnits(), "M", ri.getValue()).longValue();
    } catch (YarnException ye) {
      // memory should always be present
      initResourcesMap();
      return 0;
    }
  }
{code}
2) Don't need entries for memory/cpu in resource profile xml.
- In initResourcesMap, instead of shutdown the process, could we throw some special runtime exception? This is a bad issue for a running YARN process, but may not have to shutdown the process.
- Incompatible resource types between RM/NM/Application need to be handled in following patches.

